INSERT INTO Reviews (Id, Qualification, PositiveComment, NegativeComment, UserId, HotelId, Date) VALUES ('88c88903-b5d5-40d1-8fdb-4c159b8b6be5', 4.0, "Unfortunately we had to postpone our trip because a passport for a member of our family was late in arriving. We gave the property over three weeks notice about the problem and they were unwilling to make any sort of adjustment to our reservation. It was EXTREMELY difficult to communicate with the property managers despite reaching out to them quite a number of times and asking the same question if we could move our reservation from early June to late July. I believe that the property managers ignored our messages trying to act in good faith and change our reservation with three weeks notice. I do understand nonrefundable and cancellation policies, but we still wanted to stay at their property and pay them in full for doing so but just hoping that they would be willing to work with us and modify our reservation given that we gave them quite adequate notice of three weeks. But, based on the poor/lack of communication from the property managers, it was obvious that their perspective was that they had our money for our early June stay, didn‚Äôt care about our unfortunate circumstance of not receiving a passport in time for our departure and that if we wanted to stay at their property in late July that we could simply pay a full lodging charge for those days. At the end, it was completely our issue that one of our passports didn‚Äôt show up in time for our trip, but our experience just confirms the old adage that ‚Äúbusiness is business‚Äù and that service, understanding one‚Äôs plight and being willing to work with a new guest/customer to make an adjustment have no chance of happening in today‚Äôs world, at least certainly not at Pine Paradise by Seaside Homes.", "Property managers/owners lack of response and their unwillingness to work with us and adjust our reservation.", '3c7b4247-dc17-4866-8d85-a10ac22576cf', '5f2cd5